lines.value:
If thou art of this mind, 'twere well thou ne'er hadst sinned; 
but as it is, hear me; for that is the next best course; I in my house 
have charms to soothe thy love,-'twas but now I thought of them;-these 
shall cure thee of thy sickness on no disgraceful terms, thy mind unhurt, 
if thou wilt be but brave. But from him thou lovest we must get some token, 
word or fragment of his robe, and thereby unite in one love's twofold stream.

Lo! where himself doth come, thy son Hippolytus, in good time; 
dismiss thy hurtful rage, King Theseus, and bethink thee what is best for 
thy house,
